<task id="004" project="email-to-document-automation-r2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Add Download Audit Logging</title>
    <phase>1: Download Endpoint</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>003</dependencies>
    <blocks>005</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, api</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Task adds logging without complex code changes</rigor-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add comprehensive audit logging for all download requests to Application Insights.
    This is required for FR-03 and supports legal compliance requirements for email document access.
    Log successful downloads, failed attempts, and authorization denials.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in OpenTelemetry and Application Insights integration.
    Follow existing telemetry patterns in the codebase.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Application Insights receives audit events for:
    1. Successful downloads (documentId, userId, filename, fileSize, duration)
    2. Authorization denials (documentId, userId, reason)
    3. Not found errors (documentId, userId)
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Email documents are often legal correspondence that requires audit trails. FR-03 requires
      audit logging for all downloads. The existing EmailTelemetry class provides a pattern
      for structured telemetry in this domain.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/EmailTelemetry.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/DocumentEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Filters/DocumentDownloadAuthorizationFilter.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">MUST log to Application Insights (FR-03)</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">MUST include user identity in audit logs</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">MUST NOT log file content or sensitive data</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/api.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/EMAIL-TO-DOCUMENT-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Telemetry" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/EmailTelemetry.cs">
        Follow existing telemetry class pattern with counters and histograms
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read EmailTelemetry.cs to understand the telemetry pattern</step>
    <step order="2">Create or extend telemetry class with document download metrics</step>
    <step order="3">Add counter: document.download.requests (with tags: status, userId)</step>
    <step order="4">Add histogram: document.download.duration (ms)</step>
    <step order="5">Add counter: document.download.denied (with tag: reason)</step>
    <step order="6">Inject telemetry into DocumentEndpoints download handler</step>
    <step order="7">Inject telemetry into DocumentDownloadAuthorizationFilter</step>
    <step order="8">Verify builds and telemetry calls are in place</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change this task's status to âœ… completed</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build and verify .NET project</tool>
    <tool name="terminal">Run shell commands</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Telemetry/DocumentTelemetry.cs (new or extended)</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/DocumentEndpoints.cs (modified)</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Filters/DocumentDownloadAuthorizationFilter.cs (modified)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given a successful download, when querying Application Insights, then document.download.requests
      event exists with status=success.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Given an authorization denial, when querying Application Insights, then document.download.denied
      event exists with userId and reason.
    </criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">
      Download duration is recorded as histogram metric.
    </criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Use the existing Meter pattern from EmailTelemetry. Include correlation ID for request tracing.
    Consider using ILogger for structured logs in addition to metrics.
  </notes>

